T1	Participants 450 967	This is a randomized, double-blind, placebo-controlled, crossover study aimed to assess the efficacy and safety of Cappra(®), a traditional herbal medicine which was used in Thailand for decades, for the treatment of mild and mild to moderate ED in Thai patients. A total of 63 patients with mild or mild to moderate ED were randomized to receive Cappra(®) or placebo for two weeks in the first period, followed by one week washout period. The patients were switched to the alternative treatment in the second period.
